📚 PageTurner – Online E-commerce Book Shop
PageTurner is a full-featured online book store built using PHP, MySQL, HTML, CSS, and Bootstrap. It offers a seamless and secure shopping experience for book lovers while enabling efficient management for admins and staff.
The platform includes admin, user, and staff roles, each with customized access and functionalities.

🔧 Technologies Used
Frontend: HTML5, CSS3, Bootstrap 4

Backend: PHP (Core PHP)

Database: MySQL

Payment Gateway: Razorpay

Hosting Ready: XAMPP/LAMP/WAMP supported

🌟 Key Features
🔐 Authentication & Role Management
Role-based login for:

Admin

Staff

User

🛒 User Features
Browse books by category, author, or title

Search functionality with filters

Add books to cart and wishlist

Place orders with Razorpay integration

View order history and invoice

👨‍💼 Admin Features
Admin Dashboard with analytics

Manage:

Book inventory (CRUD)

Registered users

Staff accounts

Order status and delivery tracking

🧑‍🔧 Staff Features
View and manage book listings

Update delivery status

Assist in inventory operations

💳 Payment Integration
Razorpay used for fast, secure, and reliable payments


🏁 Getting Started
✅ Prerequisites
PHP 7.x or later

MySQL

Apache Server (XAMPP/LAMP/WAMP)

Composer (optional for dependencies)

⚙️ Installation Steps
Clone the repository:

bash
Copy
Edit
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/PageTurner-Ecommerce-Bookshop.git
Import the database:

Open phpMyAdmin

Create a new database named pageturner

Import the pageturner.sql file from the database folder

Configure database in config.php:

$host = "localhost";
$user = "root";
$pass = "";
$db = "pageturner";
$conn = mysqli_connect($host, $user, $pass, $db);
Run the project:

Start Apache and MySQL using XAMPP/WAMP

Visit http://localhost/PageTurner



